net.bytebuddy.agent.builder

Class AgentBuilder.Default.InitializationStrategy.SelfInjection

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.bytebuddy.agent.builder.AgentBuilder.Default.InitializationStrategy.SelfInjection
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    AgentBuilder.Default.InitializationStrategy, ByteCodeAppender, Implementation
    Enclosing interface:
    AgentBuilder.Default.InitializationStrategy

    public static class AgentBuilder.Default.InitializationStrategy.SelfInjection
extends Object
implements AgentBuilder.Default.InitializationStrategy, Implementation, ByteCodeAppender
    An initialization strategy that adds a code block to an instrumented type's type initializer which then calls a specific class that is responsible for the explicit initialization.

      • prepare

        public InstrumentedType prepare(InstrumentedType instrumentedType)
        Description copied from interface: Implementation
        During the preparation phase of an implementation, implementations are eligible to adding fields or methods to the currently instrumented type. All methods that are added by this implementation are required to be implemented by the ByteCodeAppender that is emitted on the call to Implementation.appender(Implementation.Target) call. On this method call, loaded type initializers can also be added to the instrumented type.
        Specified by:
        prepare in interface Implementation
        Parameters:
        instrumentedType - The instrumented type that is the basis of the ongoing instrumentation.
        Returns:
        The instrumented type with any applied changes, if any.
